To    other   languages
ASCII strings
are   translated.
By    the     GNU     C library gettext       support is provided.
By    the     gettext software  project also  support is provided.
For   non     Linux   kernel    based   POSIX support is provided?
If    this    argot   can       not     link
then  this    argot
is    not     provided.

For   script  use
non   English to  native  translation
is    not         useful  and
extra CPU         cycles
are   consumed.
But   interactive scripts sometimes exist.

